headline: Fabless future no longer unthinkable for Intel
summary: Investing.com -- Intel’s latest earnings report has reignited debate around a future without its own manufacturing. The company warned last week that it may stop pursuing nodes beyond its 18A process unless it secures a major external customer, raising the real possibility of Intel one day becoming a fabless company.
